CLI(Command Line Interface)
kubectl -- it is a CLI tool for kubernetes that starts with kubectl for all commands

To install kubectl
 go to browser -- serach with kubectl instal
  curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"--> to install kubectl
  chmod +x kubectl--> to give the x permissions
   mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/--> need to move kubectl to default path, then only it'll show as installed
   kubectl version--> to check whether installed or not
   
