If we want to attach a label to existing pod that don't have
kubectl label pod mypod "env=test"
kubectl label pod mypod course=devops cloud=aws

kubectl get po -l app=swiggy--> to get a specific app
kubectl get po -l env=test
kubectl get po -l env!=test--> we'll get otherthsn test env
ebs-- equality based selector ex: (env=test)
sbs-- set based selector ex (env in (dev,test)')
kubectl get po -l 'env in (dev,test)'--> to get set of labels

node selector is used to sleect a particular node
kubectl get no--> to check the nodes
kubectl get node nodeid node=node2--> to attach node


     
